<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="425" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="425">
A pharate female in a pupal case was identified by Botosaneanu and Alkins-Koo (1993) as &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1970" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" rank="tribe" tribe="Leucotrichiini">Leucotrichiini</taxonomicName>
-case 2&quot;. Subsequently, Flint (1996) associated this female with 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. fairchildi" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" rank="species" species="fairchildi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">L. fairchildi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in addition to collecting adult material from Trinidad and Venezuela.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
